  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective in-vitro study conducted at three independent test sites; the study protocol, instrumentation calibration records, and inter-laboratory reproducibility data are cited extensively in the decision record and are considered by the assessment team to constitute rigorous experimental corroboration of CFD predictions.",
