      "name": "Multi-site hemolysis index comparison — CFD vs. in-vitro data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values were compared against in-vitro measurements collected across three independent laboratories using the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry. All five flow-speed operating points returned RH < 1.0 relative to the predicate device. Inter-laboratory coefficient of variation was 4.2%, confirming measurement reproducibility. The assessment team notes that the prospective multi-site study design, with pre-specified acceptance thresholds and blinded CFD predictions, provides strong corroborating evidence for model fidelity under CPB conditions.",
