    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou1-cpb-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-vv-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at this risk level. The multi-site prospective study (n=75 total observations across 5 operating points × 3 sites × 5 replicates) provides extensive corroborating evidence for CFD predictions, with mean absolute relative error of 5.3% in RH well within the 15% acceptance band established in VVP-CPB-2024-03. The geometric sensitivity analysis confirms that worst-case hemolysis is correctly identified by the CFD model. The assessment team concludes that the CFD model is credible for the stated COU.",
